# Offer of Internship - AI Intern

Date: [Date]

Dear [Candidate Name],

We are pleased to offer you an internship with Omninuera as an AI Intern on the terms described below. This letter is a draft offer and should be reviewed by Legal before finalization.

## Position and Term
- Position: AI Intern.
- Duration: 3 months.
- Start date: [Start Date].
- Work location: Fully remote. Intern will be located in Bengaluru.
- Employment type: Internship (stipend, not salary).

## Reporting
- Reporting manager: [Reporting Manager Name, Title].

## Duties and Responsibilities
As an AI Intern you will typically be expected to perform duties such as:
- Assist with data collection, cleaning, annotation, and preprocessing.
- Implement, train, evaluate, and fine-tune machine learning models and pipelines.
- Develop and test model training scripts, evaluation metrics, and experiments.
- Analyze model performance, prepare visualizations and reports, and present findings.
- Collaborate with engineering teams to integrate model outputs into prototypes.
- Research and summarize relevant academic and technical literature.
- Maintain clear documentation of experiments, code, datasets, and results.
- Complete assigned deliverables and contribute to team meetings and reviews.

## Working Hours and Expectations
- Expected commitment: 20-30 hours per week.
- Maintain reasonable overlap with India Standard Time (IST) for meetings and collaboration.
- Be responsive to manager and team communication during agreed working hours.
- Deliverables and milestones will be agreed with the reporting manager and tracked throughout the internship.

## Stipend and Payment Schedule
- Stipend: INR 10,000 per month.
- Payment method: Monthly by bank transfer to the account details provided by you.
- First payment: Paid within the first month following successful onboarding and submission of bank details, covering work completed that month.
- If the internship is terminated early, stipend will be adjusted pro rata for time worked and any unearned stipend will be returned or withheld as appropriate.

## Tax Treatment
- The stipend is stipendiary and not a salary. You are responsible for your own tax compliance and reporting as required by applicable law.
- Omninuera may withhold taxes from stipend payments if required by applicable law.

## Intellectual Property and Confidentiality
- All work product, inventions, discoveries, improvements, source code, models, datasets, derivatives, training artifacts, documentation, designs, know-how, and other materials created, conceived, or reduced to practice by you, alone or jointly with others, during the internship and related to Omninuera's business or using Omninuera resources (collectively Work Product) are the exclusive property of Omninuera.
- You hereby assign and agree to assign to Omninuera all right, title, and interest in and to the Work Product worldwide, including all copyrights, patent rights, trade secret rights, moral rights to the maximum extent permitted by law, and any renewals or extensions.
- You agree that Omninuera shall have the exclusive right to use, modify, reproduce, distribute, publish, sublicense, and exploit the Work Product in any form, including code, trained models, datasets, outputs, and derivatives.
- You waive and agree not to assert any moral rights in the Work Product to the extent permissible by applicable law. Where waiver is not permitted, you agree to provide Omninuera an irrevocable, transferable, sublicensable, perpetual license to exercise such rights.
- You will promptly disclose all Work Product to Omninuera and, at Omninuera's request and expense, execute and deliver such further documents and do such further acts as may be reasonably necessary to vest ownership fully in Omninuera.
- Confidentiality: You agree to keep confidential and not disclose or use except for Omninuera's benefit any confidential or proprietary information of Omninuera, including but not limited to technical data, business plans, customer information, code, model weights, datasets, and trade secrets. This obligation continues after the internship ends.

## Background and Reference Checks
- This offer is contingent on the successful completion of satisfactory background and reference checks, including identity verification, education verification, and criminal record checks as applicable and permitted by law.
- You must provide accurate information and any documents requested to complete these checks.

## Termination
- Either party may terminate this internship with one week notice to the other party.
- Omninuera may terminate immediately for cause, including breach of confidentiality, misconduct, dishonesty, or material failure to perform duties.
- Upon termination, stipend will be paid for time worked up to the termination date and adjusted pro rata. Any overpaid or unearned stipend may be recovered by Omninuera as permitted by law.

## Compliance with Laws and Policies
- You must comply with Omninuera policies, including data protection, acceptable use, and security policies, and with applicable local laws and regulations in connection with your internship.
- Omninuera will comply with applicable employment, labor, and tax laws in jurisdictions where it operates.

## Acceptance Instructions
To accept this offer:
1. Sign and date below, then scan and email the signed offer to hr@omninuera.com, or use an e-signature method approved by Omninuera.
2. Return the signed offer by: [Offer Expiry Date].

## Miscellaneous
- This letter, once signed, constitutes the full offer for this internship. Any changes must be in writing and signed by an authorized representative of Omninuera.
- This offer does not create an obligation to continue employment beyond the internship term.

Sincerely,

Omninuera

Company Representative:
